"v.使无效；中和 【英】 v. 使无效(to make ineffective; nullify)；中和(to make neutral) 【考】 soothe: anger/neutralize: acid(抚慰消除愤怒/ 中和消除酸) 【记】 来自neutral(中性的) +ize 【例】 to neutralize an acid with a base v. 使无效; 中和 【记】源于: neutral(n 中立者; adj 中立的; 中性的) 【参】neutron(n 中子) 【类】soothe: anger = neutralize: acid[effectiveness]抚慰消除愤怒 = 中和消除酸性[效力] 【记】neutral 中立的 neutralize (v.)  1734, ""to render neutral"" (in a chemical sense), from French neutraliser (17c.), from neutral (see neutral (adj.)). Meaning ""to counterbalance, to kill by opposing"" is from 1795. Related: Neutralized; neutralizing."
